eu_initiatives:
We follow all developments related to the EU relations with Armenia and its region, including: 
- the EU- Armenia negotiations for a new framework agreement; 
- the developments related  to the Eastern Partnership, especially those processes involving Armenia; 
- the developments related to European Neighbourhood Policy in general, including the Single Support Framework for EU support to Armenia; 
- all processes related to the promotion of Democracy, Human Rights and the Rule of Law, especially those focusing in Armenia and/or the South Caucasus Region.

relevant_communication:
- EU-Armenia agenda: we work with all European institutions; 
-Providing background information: on a regular basis, we organise roundtables with experts and high level decision makers from EU and Armenian institutions as well as civil society representatives; 
-Besides, we regularly publish shortpapers on issues relevant for the relations between Armenia and Europe (cf. www.eufoa.org); 
- Finally, we keep close ties with a large number of civil society organisations in Europe and Armenia as far as they work on issues connected to Armenia’s relations with Europe; 
-We also provide logistical help for trips of representatives from think-tanks, academia and media to Armenia;
